---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';

const relatedPages = [
  { title: "TUI Reference", description: "Panes, shortcuts, capture", href: "/docs/tui" },
  { title: "Tack", description: "The operator intent language", href: "/features/tack" },
  { title: "Commands", description: "Full CLI reference", href: "/docs/commands" },
];
---

<FeaturePage
  tagline="FEATURE // INTERFACE"
  title="AI Agent Terminal Dashboard"
  description="Terminal interface showing the OS in real time. Agents, permissions, edits, costs — all visible. The operator sees everything."
  relatedPages={relatedPages}
>
  <h2>What you see</h2>
  <p>
    Launch <code>ostk tui</code> and the terminal becomes a command deck. Fleet status in one pane, audit events in another, needle backlog below, tack bar at the bottom. Every agent action surfaces in real time.
  </p>

  <h2>Panes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>FLEET</strong> — Running agents with status indicators: ● active, ○ stale, ✕ crashed</li>
    <li><strong>ACTIVITY</strong> — Last 10 audit events. What just happened.</li>
    <li><strong>WORK</strong> — Needle backlog sorted by priority (P0→P3)</li>
    <li><strong>METRICS</strong> — Token savings, compression ratio, cache hit rate</li>
    <li><strong>TACK BAR</strong> — Multi-line intent editor for operator commands</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Permission gates</h2>
  <p>
    When an agent requests a tool that needs approval, a modal appears with the agent alias, tool name, and input preview. Press <code>y</code> to approve, <code>n</code> to deny, <code>a</code> to approve all for that capability class. <strong>Enter defaults to deny</strong> — hitting return without thinking rejects the call. This is a safety default: a distracted operator's reflex should never be to approve. Source: <code>src/fcp_screen/action.rs:286</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Capture</h2>
  <p>
    Record terminal sessions as asciicast v2 files with <code>:capture</code>. The TeeWriter clones raw ANSI bytes to a background thread — zero disruption to the render pipeline. Status bar shows [*] when recording.
  </p>
</FeaturePage>
